issue.title: Replace custom POW! Angels code with a service
issue.body:
I think it stands between Podia and Patreon.

Patreon is very much about rewards, but could of course not promise much at each tire. It is branded Patreon. This could be both seen as good and bad.

Podia is a membership and course platform.

Both will let med do public and Angel only content. However, with Podia, I could also develop small courses and digital downloads only the Angels would get access to. And I think that sort of content could be the reward they get.

issue.title: State / Storage handling
issue.body:
Using this approach as of now: https://blog.usejournal.com/react-hooks-the-rebirth-of-state-management-and-beyond-7d84f6026d87

Not liking it, really miss my Redux reducers and Redux Observables. However, I feel like that might be overkill for this project.

It syncs on every change and uses a timestamp to merge potentially newer data from Gaia. It seems to work pretty well, but not too happy with it.

I would like data to be stored encrypted in local storage, so the app will work offline, as well as syncing to Gaia storage to let the users switch devices. I think a local first approach would make the most sense as I am guessing most users will use their personal phones 90% of the time. I heard about [Conflict-free replicated data type (CRDT)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conflict-free_replicated_data_type) on [Full Stack Radio](http://www.fullstackradio.com/126) and it sounded like the type of approach that could work for POW!.
